Hello,
{pp}
My name is Michal Bergseth, 23 years old and oldtime Amiga user. I own
www.amigaworld.org and it started up not so long ago. 23.04.03 to
be correct. Its been on-line before, but because of problems with the
hosted webserver for a year ago. Its been a bit hard for the new
webhost company here in Norway to get it to me.
{pp}
I also do a Amiga magazine here in Scandinavia, called Amitopia. So
www.amigaworld.org is a part of Amitopia. The articles that we get for
Amitopia, will after 4-5 weeks be on-line for everyone. AmigaWorld does
also give guides and tips on how to improove and give Amigas
a better life. hehe :)
{pp}
Well, now its all oki and AmigaWorld Magazine is on-line!
{pp}
If you feel that you want to write for AmigaWorld.org or maybe our magazine
could use your articles and so on? Thats all up
to you offcourse. I would like to takeover for you. If there are some
contributors or will to contribute. Youre all welcome!
{pp}
Regards,{p}
Michal, editor of Amitopia and webmaster of AmigaWorld Magazine{p}
